data.name: legendaryToLegendaryCheck.ToolTip
data.value: When randomizing legendaries on trainers, randomize them into other legendaries. No more final battles with cascoon. Note: If using "No Duplicates" and all legendaries have been picked, this will pick a duplicate legendary.

data.name: noDuplicateShadowPokemonCheck.ToolTip
data.value: Picks unique shadow pokemon for each slot available Note: This setting may be ignored if other settings prevent a non-duplicate from being picked. i.e., if we've picked all the available pokemon with respect to our settings, then this will pick a duplicate just so it can continue randomizing

data.name: useSimilarBSTsCheck.ToolTip
data.value: When picking a new random pokemon, use one that has a similar BST to the current pokemon. Note: This will gradually widen the BST range to search for if none are found. Note: If using force fully evolved, this may pick a lower stage with similar BST then evolve it

data.name: trainerCatchRateComboBox.ToolTip
data.value:
Adjusts the Shadow Catch Rate on trainer Pokemon. The Shadow Catch Rate is not the same as the Pokemon's true catch rate. It's used as an in-game difficulty curve to make later encounters more difficult to capture.
- None Leave as is. This means late game encounters will be as difficult as in the vanilla game regardless of the Pokemon.
- Minimum Set a minimum catch rate that a Pokemon must have. From 1 - 255.
- True Use the set Pokemon's actual catch rate.
- Adjusted Calculates the % between the Shadow Catch Rate and the original Pokemon's true catch rate and applies it to the new Pokemon's catch rate.

data.name: tradeUsePokeSpotCheck.ToolTip
data.value: Will set the requested Pokemon in a trade to one of the PokeSpot Pokemon. Recommended if randomizing PokeSpots or trades. If randomizing PokeSpots, it may be impossible to find Duking's requested Pokemon and if randomizing trades.

data.name: forceFourMoveCheck.ToolTip
data.value: If not randomizing the movesets, some Pokemon's level up moves don't have enough at their level. Selecting this will ensure that all Pokemon will have four moves. Will randomly pick moves to fill out the rest.

data.name: randomizeMovesetsOnlyLegal.ToolTip
data.value: Randomly pick a moveset from moves a Pokemon learns via level up, TM or Tutor Move Note: If TM/Tutor Moves are randomized, then it may pick a move that's technically not legal for a Pokemon to learn in the vanilla games.

data.name: martsSellEvoStonesCheck.ToolTip
data.value: Agate Village mart sells evolution stones for 2100. Note: Sun Stones sell for 500 and Moon stones sell for 0. I haven't altered any of the selling prices for them. Note: This option doesn't work properly on EU

data.name: banBadItemsCheck.ToolTip
data.value: Bans items that aren't very useful in Colo/XD. This includes all berries, contest items, shards (except moon and sun), and items that have to do with wild pokemon (e.g. repels, pokedolls, smoke ball, etc.)

data.name: prngDropDown.ToolTip
data.value: Select a random generator to use. Net: Built-in PRNG, tends to have duplicates Xoroshiro128: Custom PRNG, has better results but still limited by being a PRNG Cryptographic: Truly random, the best randomness at the cost of not being able to specify a seed
